Mathare MP Stephen Kariuki yesterday dismissed allegations by a group of youths and Jubilee MCAs that he swindled Sh1 million during a rally in Mathare.The youths say Kariuki received cash from top Jubilee Party leaders for the rally that was held on the same day as Cord&rsquo;s meeting on September 18.The first term MP, who decamped from Cord, said he used his own money to organise for the rally. &ldquo;I had a very successful meeting using my resources. Anyone can claim what they want. It&rsquo;s politics and we are used to it,&rdquo; he said.